1492518600.sessionTitle: Introduction to the Camera Effects Platform
1492518600.sessionDescription: Come hear more about Camera Effects Platform, a suite of creative tools that lets you create effects for the Facebook camera, from simple photo frames to interactive masks and effects that use Augmented Reality (AR). In this session you’ll learn what camera effects are, how to create and submit your own, and how you can connect with the audiences that matter to you by providing rich experiences that help them express themselves.

1492518600.sessionTitle: Growth Marketing: Best Practices for Getting and Keeping an Audience
1492518600.sessionDescription: Even the most successful apps must constantly work to build and maintain their customer bases. Join Facebook’s growth marketing experts for best practices in acquisition, optimization, engagement and virality.

ogImage.name: c8aefaf8e2a63d4c2e0ed97e8d60d61e_Growth Marketing Best Practices for Getting and Keeping an Audience.png

1492518600.sessionTitle: Litho: A Declarative Framework for Efficient UIs
1492518600.sessionDescription: Components for Android allows developers to implement complex, efficient RecyclerViews through a simple declarative API. In this session we’ll discuss the function and features of this powerful framework.

ogImage.name: cd8a1af8c9415e34d34da29d5c445c6d_Litho A Declarative Framework for Efficient UIs.png

1492518600.sessionTitle: WebVR: Enabling Developers to Build Engaging Cross-Platform VR Content
1492518600.sessionDescription: Web-based frameworks such as React VR are making it easier than ever to create VR content that can be shared with a huge audience across VR, mobile, and the web. Coupled with the new web browser that Oculus is building, more of the web will become immersive over the coming years. Join us to learn what you can build with WebVR and how this new technology can help enhance your existing content.

ogImage.name: e7367d84d0bd1d44a609b60ef8dc955c_WebVR Enabling Developers to Build Engaging CrossPlatform VR Content.png

1492518600.sessionDescription: Facebook Messenger connects over a billion people around the world. For marketers and bot builders, this session presents best practices and tips for engaging your audience with Messenger.

Chris Cox, Facebook's Chief Product Officer, explores the role media plays on Facebook and what we're learning from our community. Dan Rose, VP of Partnerships, will share how we're partnering with our media partners to deliver business value.

1492520400.sessionTitle: How to Build a Great Bot
1492520400.sessionDescription: Understand the features and technology available to developers in Messenger. Engineers and bot developers, join us for a technical deep dive, including best practices on major features, and updates on the latest in the Messenger Platform.

1492522200.sessionTitle: The Evolution of React and GraphQL at Facebook and Beyond
1492522200.sessionDescription: With cutting-edge rendering and data-fetching, React and GraphQL continue to revolutionize modern apps. In this session, we’ll discuss new developments in these frameworks that will help improve performance in the next evolution of app design.

ogImage.name: e7be563c1e57e96f2cb9a9a8b81302a6_The evolution of react and graphql at facebook and beyond.png

1492522200.sessionTitle: Bringing VR Experiences to Everyone: Scripting, Producing and Planning
1492522200.sessionDescription: Learn how to develop a VR experience, and take a project from creative idea to a piece ready for prime time. Gain best practices and tips and tricks for producing experiences, how to approach acting and directing in VR, and distribution.

ogImage.name: 5a914873d87d7cbf1cb843f76db6fdb4_Bringing VR Experiences to Everyone Scripting Producing and Planning.png

1492522200.sessionTitle: Building Native Games for Facebook Gameroom
1492522200.sessionDescription: Facebook Gameroom helps you build your business and connect with highly engaged players on a new gaming platform dedicated to gaming. Join us to learn top tips on how to get started with the SDK, publish native games, and take advantage of services like hosting.
Adam Mosseri, VP, News Feed, will dive into how News Feed works so publishers can more effectively reach their audiences.

How does one succeed in creating products for a world that is increasingly divided? Bold ideas are proposed, changes in Southeast Asia, and personal confessions from Khailee Ng's journey from petty crimes to repeatedly creating successful startups in emerging markets.

1492522200.sessionTitle: Intro to Building Camera Effects with the AR Studio: Live Demo
1492522200.sessionDescription: Facebook's Camera Effects Platform includes AR Studio, a new tool that lets 3D artists and developers create interactive photo and video effects for the new Facebook camera. 1492524000.sessionTitle: What's Next for Workplace by Facebook?

1492524000.sessionTitle: A Startup Journey from an Emerging Market

speakers.speakerTitle: VP of Business Development, Fandango Latam

1492525800.sessionDescription: Yarn and Jest are popular and widely adopted open source projects. In this session, we’ll present our roadmap for these projects and share our experiences – good and bad – in releasing and maintaining popular open source projects.

Distribution on mobile is exceptionally difficult. Come hear about Facebook’s latest way of solving mobile game distribution in a fun way that brings people together to play and compete across our social platforms.

1492525800.sessionTitle: The Future of Video on Facebook
1492525800.sessionDescription: Video is playing an increasingly important role in connecting people. Learn how we're bringing video to the forefront of the Facebook experience and harnessing the power of the Facebook community to drive discovery, consumption, discussion, and sharing of video.

ogImage.name: f4771692d39a9daac2347c3f97e1824b_The Future of Video on Facebook.png

1492525800.sessionTitle: React VR: Build amazing VR experiences using React
1492525800.sessionDescription: Learn how React VR builds upon React Native, and how the supporting layers and libraries interact. We will take you through a sample VR web app built with React VR, and show how easy it is to create immersive experiences across VR, mobile, and web.

ogImage.name: b8fb801d41d0357c69e718e38e1ff3ca_React VR Build amazing VR experiences using React.png

ogImage.name: 4674a45764c2cac0a5d5608e84a72589_What can be Learned from China Mobile Economy Boom in Past 5 Years.png

1492525800.sessionDescription: There’s been 110 billion-dollar tech startups since 2010, and behind them lies the whole route of China's mobile economy boom. With a highly connected and digitalized social environment, it’s possible to fill big gaps of user demands in a more efficient and intelligent way - a pattern that can be repeated.

1492527600.sessionDescription: With AI that transforms images, Facebook’s Camera Effects Platform lets you create animated masks, interactive overlays, frames, and other effects that people can apply to their photos and videos in the Facebook camera. Learn best technical and design practices for creating effects using this innovative technology, and see examples of successful effects.

A behind-the-scenes look at how we built Facebook Spaces, the new immersive social VR experience from Facebook. We’ll walk through major product features and how they were developed, sharing the lessons we learned about how to create compelling social experiences in VR.

1492527600.sessionTitle: Building Custom Integrations for Workplace by Facebook
1492527600.sessionDescription: Workplace by Facebook can revolutionize the way your company works together. Join us for a technical deep dive and a first look at the new integrations announced for bots in groups and Work Chat, and tips on how to build more effective bots.

ogImage.name: b5a12b506b5f315846ed46cf869c950c_Building Custom Integrations for Workplace by Facebook.png

1492529400.sessionDescription: Who streams their gameplay live, and why? Join a former pro gamer and veteran streamer to explore why people stream, and who’s watching. If you’ve thought about adding live streaming to your game, this talk is for you.

In a world where video is the primary format, what kind of content works well? We'll talk about the types of creative that drive community and engagement and hear from special guests on how they think about this.

Learn about the unique scaling challenges encountered when developing Hack, the programming language behind Facebook.com. We’ll share the story of how we migrated from millions of lines of PHP, engineering through the problems that only come with a rapidly evolving codebase

1492531200.sessionTitle: Moving Faster: Optimizing Developer Experiences of Facebook Engineers
1492531200.sessionDescription: At Facebook, we help developers move fast by providing them with powerful tools. We'll take a look at how Facebook optimizes developer workflows today, and will explore the use of deep learning to power the next wave of advances.

ogImage.name: 8a603cc3d9449f124d7e2eadc10064da_Moving Faster Optimizing Developer Experiences of Facebook Engineers.png

1492531200.sessionDescription: Power your app with the Places Graph. We're providing free access to the same place data that powers Facebook, Instagram, and Messenger. Learn how to use data about 140M+ places around the world to create location aware app experiences.

ogImage.name: 4a4615a3b429fad7b31fe3ed77df18db_Explore the Power of the Places Graph.png

1492531200.sessionTitle: Create Fullscreen Experiences On Mobile with Canvas
1492531200.sessionDescription: Canvas is an immersive platform that makes it simple to create fullscreen, engaging experiences on mobile. In this session, we’ll share tips for easily creating your own Canvas, along with highlights from partner integrations on the Canvas API.

1492531200.sessionTitle: International Research: Gaining Cultural Context for Scalable Solutions.
1492531200.sessionDescription: Building products for unfamiliar markets is challenging, and there are many factors to take into consideration before getting started. Hear the process the Facebook Research team follows to guide product development for new markets.

ogImage.name: 5837693e33af8a8b33e5f251d2f19658_International Research Gaining Cultural Context for Scalable Solutions..png

1492531200.sessionTitle: Early Lessons in Social VR from Oculus Rooms
1492531200.sessionDescription: We’ve already learned a lot since launching Oculus Rooms. We’ll share insights from our research and observations on what works, what doesn’t, and how people interact together in Rooms — plus the latest features we’ve added to the experience.

ogImage.name: 1aefdcb332769cdd96d4405d67b9155b_Early Lessons in Social VR from Oculus Rooms.png

1492533000.sessionDescription: Wondering how you can boost your productivity and maximize your impact as a developer? Come to this session to learn about best practices and new updates to the Graph API and developer tools.

ogImage.name: bbc1181218b9ebb4c80f8a9e07f806a3_best practices for integrating facebook technologies into your product.png

1492533000.sessionDescription: Over the last year, we've made product improvements to Facebook Login and Account Kit based on insights on consumer preferences and market trends. Learn about the impact these could have on your business along with coding demos on how to integrate these exciting features into your apps.

1492533000.sessionTitle: Measure the Complete Customer Journey with Facebook Analytics
1492533000.sessionDescription: People use multiple channels across different devices throughout their customer journey. Learn how Facebook Analytics can help you simplify measurement with powerful omni-channel analytics.

ogImage.name: 6ed24862984f442edf2427db00b2f841_Measure the Complete Customer Journey with Facebook Analytics for Apps .png

1492533000.sessionDescription: Facebook is committed to accessibility. In this session we’ll discuss how we’re helping engineers identify problem areas for accessibility and implement fixes with Stetho, our open source Android debugging tool.

1492533000.sessionTitle: The Future of Monetizing with Audience Network
1492533000.sessionDescription: The monetization ecosystem is ever changing and complex, leaving mobile developers and publishers struggling to find the right solutions to maximize monetization and user experience. Learn how Audience Network is helping developers and publishers tackle these challenges today, and into the future.

ogImage.name: 9102aeb5aa6e96aca4641074e404f51d_The Future of Monetizing with Audience Network.png

1492533000.sessionDescription: Our partners are investing heavily in video. We want to help them achieve a sustainable return on that investment, both on Facebook and on their own sites. Executives from three different publishers will talk about what they've learned in testing some of our latest monetization features.

1492534800.sessionDescription: Like. Love. Haha. Wow. Sad. Angry. Join engineers who worked on Facebook's reactions for an inside peek at how Facebook launches a brand new feature to the world.

Maintaining a connection with high-value customers after download is key to your app’s success. Learn how mobile app ads’ sophisticated targeting and optimization help you reach these customers and grow your app.

1492536600.sessionDescription: Privacy by design is a key part of the entire product lifecycle at Facebook. We'll discuss the role privacy plays in product development, and how we communicate about it on an ongoing basis.
Insights from research guide good business decisions. In this session, we’ll discuss creative methods used at Facebook for conducting research to help you get deeper, more engaging insights.

Maintaining account security goes beyond the login process: learn how trusted identities by sites like Facebook can make account recovery more efficient, more secure, and easier to manage for developers—all while putting privacy front and center.

Instagram’s mission is to help people connect through shared experiences. 80% of the community is outside of the US, and as our platform grows, Instagram must perform across an increasing variety of devices and networks to keep people connected. For people in low-bandwidth regions, we’ve begun testing offline experiences that keep the Instagram experience consistent and let people consume and engage with content, even if they don’t have service. In this talk we’ll introduce some of our initial explorations into offline features, and share learnings you can apply to your own apps.

1492536600.sessionTitle: Fireside Chat: The Future of Media
1492536600.sessionDescription: Join us for a discussion on the future of media with Fidji Simo, VP of Media Products at Facebook, and James Gunn, Writer and Director, Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2.

speakers.speakerTitle: Writer and Director, Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2

1492603200.sessionDescription: Come to our panel to learn from bot builders and innovators about strategies to build and grow a successful bot.

1492605000.sessionTitle: Build Meaningful Customer Connections with Facebook
1492605000.sessionDescription: We show you how to provide an experience for your customers that is consistent, safe, and delightful across channels and throughout their journey with your business.

The real world is immersive. It has depth. It's 3D. x24 and x6, the newest designs in the Surround 360 family, are making it possible to bring all this rich detail to life in live-action VR. In this talk, we detail the new technology and how it might change storytelling.

1492605000.sessionTitle: Using Machine Translation to Remove Language Barriers on Facebook
1492605000.sessionDescription: Deep learning has profoundly shaped the translation process. Join us as we discuss the unique challenges faced in translation, difficulties with neural networks, how these challenges were overcome, and future applications of deep learning in translation.

ogImage.name: b1c421e64c038f005fa5b208326670ff_Using Machine Translation to Remove Language Barriers on Facebook.png

1492605000.sessionTitle: How WhatsApp Reduced Spam for Over 1 Billion People
1492605000.sessionDescription: Building a spam detection system for an end-to-end encrypted messaging system serving over 1 billion people worldwide is no small task. Get a behind-the-scenes look at how the anti-spam team designed scalable ways to detect and prevent abuse.

ogImage.name: 01bde1e7e0421eb0a5305a991c470798_How WhatsApp Reduced Spam for Over 1 Billion People.png

1492606800.sessionDescription: Businesses worldwide are connecting with millions of potential customers through Instagram. Learn how Instagram is using the power of visual storytelling to help businesses strengthen relationships with customers and find new ones through business tools, shopping and Instagram Stories.

Sit down with best-in-class VR filmmakers to learn what it takes to create amazing VR experiences. Whether you’re working on a 360 video or real-time rendered content, these tips will help you to understand best practices from the cutting edge of VR.

Filmmaker and VR Director, Fistful of Stars

1492608600.sessionDescription: Analytics can provide powerful insights to help you grow. Learn how you can save time, make better decisions, optimize your product, and win with Facebook Analytics.

1492608600.sessionTitle: Making the Facebook Social Graph Semantic
1492608600.sessionDescription: As media content grows on FB, we are investing in new ways for engineering teams to harness the power of computer vision for their products and services without the need for prior expertise. Come for a sneak peek into how we're advancing this framework for video products, which has both multimodal and time complexities.

1492608600.sessionDescription: 360 Capture SDK makes it accessible for people to capture and share their VR experience through a 360 photo or video on Facebook. Find out about using this SDK in VR titles.

ogImage.name: 328853c158f69ec860f5fd03c5ae9e17_The Engineering Behind Shared 360 Photos and Videos.png

1492610400.sessionTitle: Marketing API's: The Automation Advantage, for All
1492610400.sessionDescription: Facebook's Marketing API enables developers and businesses to deliver solutions beyond the capabilities of traditional marketers. Learn how Netflix used the Marketing API’s to automate their ads management process and drive better ads performance.

ogImage.name: b201b1f1013f9e7cb817d02f0306a00e_Marketing API The Automation Advantage for All.png

1492610400.sessionDescription: Interactive and fun social experiences foster greater consumer engagement in VR. This talk will focus on the APIs and features that Oculus provides to add a social layer to your app, including the Avatar SDK, VoIP, Invites, and Oculus Rooms.

ogImage.name: 7d9883aa21d5b28b8c6f92d6993a02a6_VR Together Adding Social Components to Your VR Apps.png

This session will look at traditional scene capture through images and the ability to, for the first time, add depth and context to images and applying them in VR + Feed

People use Facebook to discover and engage with products and services, increasingly on mobile.  Hear tips to help businesses drive discovery and sales on Facebook.

1492614000.sessionDescription: As web services shifted to mobile, machine-learning was left in the data centers. We’ve moved ML to the phone, launching a full machine-learning runtime inside Facebook. Come learn what we’ve built, how it’s used, and what it means for developers.

ogImage.name: 961d9ed44002b8fe533e9b29b512c69b_Delivering Real-Time AI in the Palm of Your Hand .png

speakers.speakerTitle: Head of Development Engineering for Mobile, Oculus

ogImage.name: ccd90ee7f4d836c1b80945916740dee8_VR 201 Lessons from the Frontlines of VR Gaming.png

1492615800.sessionTitle: Building for a Billion People: Behind the Scenes with Facebook's Product Engineers
1492615800.sessionDescription: In this talk, we will explain how we have managed to maintain a culture of speed while staying in tune with our global and diverse user base, testing and shipping new features and improvements that work for everyone around the globe.

ogImage.name: a6220281dbc8590ca5fcdc453e433708_Building for a Billion People Behind the Scenes with Facebook Product Engineers.png
